('d815c0f3-352d-4a1a-96e7-1175a62ab53e',450923,'The reverse mullett model of software engineering',replace('<p>If you’ve been laid off or you’re just sweating the possibility, <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2022/12/05/just-laid-off-nervous-about-possible-layoffs-heres-what-to-do/">here’s what to do</a>. </p><p>Check out <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/10/26/hopping-instead-of-hustling-survey-tells-us-how-developers-are-taking-care-of-business/">the results</a> of our last job market survey. </p><p>Connect with Patrick on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/patrick-carlile-48181b3/">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p>Shoutout to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1099089/stevenkucera">stevenkucera</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/36/stellar-question">Stellar Question badge</a> with <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27791532/how-do-i-create-a-global-mutable-singleton">How do I create a global, mutable singleton?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/3fb6317b-92fb-4c4b-8739-fa02f87a77d2/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=3fb6317b-92fb-4c4b-8739-fa02f87a77d2&feed=XA_851k3',1714710000,1381,0,698,0),
('82200a19-7cac-41d1-8967-bee374d16993',450923,'Supporting the world’s most-used database engine through 2050',replace('<p><a href="https://www.sqlite.org/index.html">SQLite</a> is the most used database engine in the world. </p><p>Stop by the <a href="https://sqlite.org/forum/forum">forum</a> or explore the <a href="https://www.sqlite.org/docs.html">docs</a>.</p><p>Devs have pledged to support SQLite <a href="https://www.sqlite.org/lts.html">through the year 2050</a>. </p><p>The developer with a team of three, all of them himself at different points in time, was <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2021/12/31/700000-lines-of-code-20-years-and-one-developer-how-dwarf-fortress-is-built/#wp-comment-2084959">Tarn Adams of Dwarf Fortress</a> fame. </p><p>On Stack Overflow, 1.2 million people have found the answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/82875/how-can-i-list-the-tables-in-a-sqlite-database-file-that-was-opened-with-attach">How can I list the tables in a SQLite database file that was opened with ATTACH?</a>. </p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/b7de52b9-ddc1-47f2-b0d4-a79a20853fbc/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=b7de52b9-ddc1-47f2-b0d4-a79a20853fbc&feed=XA_851k3',1714105200,1729,0,696,0),
('c8025d8f-667c-4eec-b2c5-bd27d8938ec7',450923,'Is GenAI the next dot-com bubble?',replace('<p>Meta’s open-source Llama 3 model puts Meta’s AI assistant <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/18/24133808/meta-ai-assistant-llama-3-chatgpt-openai-rival">head-to-head with ChatGPT</a>.</p><p>Stability AI <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/18/24133996/stability-ai-lay-off-emad-mostaque">laid off</a> 10% of its workforce, the first major AI foundation model to reduce its workforce since the advent of generative AI.</p><p>Is the dot-com bubble a cautionary tale for AI enthusiasts? <a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/381444600/marketplace">Listen to the episode</a> of Marketplace from NPR.</p><p><a href="https://philosophy.stackexchange.com/questions/112021/does-the-success-of-ai-large-language-models-support-wittgensteins-position-t">Do LLMs support Wittgenstein’s position that “meaning is use”?</a> That depends whether you’re talking pre or post <i>Tractatus</i>, of course.</p><p>TikTok wouldn’t lie to you: you really can <a href="https://www.technologyreview.com/2022/10/31/1062370/how-to-befriend-a-crow-crowtok-tiktok/">make friends with your local crows</a>. Eira’s proven method for befriending crows: Feed them dry cat food on a consistent schedule, so they learn you’re reliable, and watch them eat, so they grok that you are feeding them intentionally.</p><p>Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/2133484/arman-ordookhani">Arman Ordookhani</a> received a well-deserved <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> for telling nearly 30,000 people <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/47979203/how-to-free-memory-in-go">How to free memory in go</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/aafa5c12-9b76-4561-a3cc-88de5871f053/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=aafa5c12-9b76-4561-a3cc-88de5871f053&feed=XA_851k3',1713875100,1475,0,695,0),
('1c9b30c0-ae63-4167-9cf6-06e333325c94',450923,'Why configuration is so complicated',replace('<p>Why can’t <a href="https://mark-burgess-oslo-mb.medium.com/why-cant-configuration-be-made-simple-16eb70ed5455">configuration be made simple</a>? </p><p>Apple is making it easier for users to <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/11/24127278/apple-iphone-repair-used-parts">repair their iPhones with used parts</a>.</p><p>Texas is <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/10/24126206/texas-staar-exam-graders-ai-automated-scoring-engine">swapping human graders for AI</a>.</p><p>Automattic (owner of WordPress) is <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/04/09/wordpress-com-owner-automattic-acquires-multi-service-messaging-app-beeper-for-125m/?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAE4eQ0XLijDIe57gP_qJNDZrcXJLaeXVJnQWP02-MhexC86NMmKjstwTS8N_y04VD5GJUOb2oIiMx91gbGMpZ8odK31p3K0VM6glPk586DGFPj__CiV1a6QK7so1oVqxACufJ5uwu9X9RqcOhMZuJ-5yx7OwPu3jeWWn3Fgb_bzR">acquiring Beeper for $125M</a>.</p><p>Silicon Valley or not, San Francisco’s train system <a href="https://www.wired.com/story/san-francisco-muni-trains-floppy-disks/">still uses floppy disks</a>. But don’t worry, an upgrade is coming—in 2030.</p><p>Shoutout to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/9951/bite-code">Bite code</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/36/stellar-question">Stellar Question badge</a> with <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2432764/how-do-i-change-the-uri-url-for-a-remote-git-repository">How do I change the URI (URL) for a remote Git repository?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/a23de6d6-005c-44cb-91ee-4fde30237654/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=a23de6d6-005c-44cb-91ee-4fde30237654&feed=XA_851k3',1713500400,1043,0,694,0),
('014d3d8f-f368-4fdb-a3d1-cf15be40261e',450923,'If everyone is building AI, why aren''t more projects in production?',replace('<p>Get started with <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/mongodb-on-google-cloud">MongoDB Atlas on Google Cloud</a> today. </p><p>Read more from the MongoDB DevRel team at <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/developer/">the MongoDB Developer Center</a>.</p><p>Learn more about Google’s <a href="https://ai.google.dev/models/gemini">Gemini models</a>. </p><p>Shout out to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/186836/thitemple">thitemple</a> for their <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat</a>-worthy answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41882174/in-typescript-how-do-i-declare-a-function-that-returns-a-string-type-array/41882274#41882274">In TypeScript, how do I declare a function that returns a string type array?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/d0d08664-1aff-4f74-8107-475f389207d1/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=d0d08664-1aff-4f74-8107-475f389207d1&feed=XA_851k3',1713327600,2498,0,693,0),
('b1b572c2-5ca1-4099-9748-30c013842bde',450923,'Climbing the GenAI decision tree',replace('<p>Learn more about the potential of <a href="https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/topic-technology/edge-5g/open-potential.html?utm_campaign=edge_ai&utm_source=Stack_Overflow&utm_medium=Podcast&utm_content=Stack&utm_term=end">AI inference with OpenVINO Notebooks</a>.</p><p>Check out the <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2024/02/28/optimizing-both-hardware-and-software-for-genai/">previous podcast with Intel</a>, where we talk with Raymond Lo about how hardware and software work together with AI.</p><p>Connect with Ria on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ria-cheruvu-54348a173/">LinkedIn</a> or <a href="https://github.com/riacheruvu">GitHub</a>. </p><p>Congrats to Lifeboat badge winner <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/953482/kevin">Kevin</a>, who showed what they know about <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/29943146/typeerror-must-use-key-word-argument-or-key-function-in-python-3-x/29944332#29944332">TypeError; Must use key word argument or key function in Python 3.x</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/0d6cfc46-0a9c-43c0-8d46-fbf878ebe78f/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=0d6cfc46-0a9c-43c0-8d46-fbf878ebe78f&feed=XA_851k3',1712722800,1546,0,690,0),
('68813fb8-cf48-4d30-8428-04baf01ee2df',450923,'What a year building AI has taught Stack Overflow',replace('<p>You can find Jessica on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/norfleetclark/">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p>We''ve published several posts, including <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2024/02/29/defining-socially-responsible-ai-how-we-select-api-partners/">this most recent one</a>, about our attempt to shape an ethical approach to combining our community of knowledge and today''s AI systems.</p><p>Check out <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/05/29/more-on-our-ai-future-building-course-recommendations-and-a-new-data-platform/">this blog post</a> that details some of the work we did to build our data platform. </p><p>Congrats to macfij on your lifeboat badge for answering the question: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/25365049/how-can-i-do-a-ctrl-a-and-a-ctrl-c/25365189#25365189">How can I do a CTRL + A and a CTRL + C?</a></p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/b8bd9923-58fa-47dd-ab93-617097fca77c/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=b8bd9923-58fa-47dd-ab93-617097fca77c&feed=XA_851k3',1712349528,1360,0,688,0),
('db7a06c8-b502-4770-b853-51a87e856f9c',450923,'Are long context windows the end of RAG?',replace('<p><a href="https://www.databricks.com/blog/introducing-dbrx-new-state-art-open-llm">DBRX</a>, an open, general-purpose LLM created by Databricks, reportedly outperforms GPT-3.5 and is competitive with Gemini 1.0 Pro.</p><p><a href="https://news.mit.edu/2024/large-language-models-use-surprisingly-simple-mechanism-retrieve-stored-knowledge-0325">Recent research</a> found that large, complex LLMs use a simple mechanism to retrieve stored knowledge in response to a user prompt. These mechanisms can help researchers reveal what the model knows and potentially even correct false information it has stored.</p><p>FTX co-founder Sam Bankman-Fried, whose downfall began in late 2022, <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/28/24112507/sam-bankman-fried-sentence-ftx-alameda">was sentenced</a> last week to 25 years in prison for conspiracy and fraud. </p><p>Find Michael on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-foree-22b78111/">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p>Find Cassidy on <a href="https://cassidoo.co/">her website</a>.</p><p>Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/971246/bucket">Bucket</a> received a well-deserved <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> for rescuing <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/37529664/how-to-calculate-decimalx-y-max-value-in-sql-server">How to calculate decimal(x, y) max value in SQL Server</a> from an ocean of ignorance.</p><p>Chapters (please note that these timestamps may not be exact): </p><p>00:00 Introduction and White Paper Discussion</p><p>02:01 Long Context Windows and Retrieval Augmented Generation</p><p>05:56 Models'' Ability to Recall Relevant Information</p><p>07:18 Models'' Creativity and Thinking Outside the Box</p><p>09:41 Advantages and Limitations of Models'' Knowledge</p><p>15:09 Databricks'' Open Language Model</p><p>22:25 Sam Bankman-Fried’s Sentence and the Effects 