('bd18afd2-5cfc-4f67-856a-265a5494c30f',450923,'Want to be a great software engineer? Don’t be a jerk.',replace('<p>A developer discovered a <a href="https://cybernews.com/editorial/xz-linux-backdoor-explained/">backdoor</a> in XZ, a popular open-source compression utility. Read more about the cyberattack <a href="https://boehs.org/node/everything-i-know-about-the-xz-backdoor?fbclid=IwAR12WI8Q5mlVTfR96aOj6B6Xm2ulAi---eLS8LelU3w661OlTh70ldF4a-A_aem_ARc8um12YBHJx9eaZlOkyCEYoxlaWtptRPh9w_2mgUOvHDWfOR8YTxwfJANYA96rEoU3Sq2DH0b3EDt6KUDtLQ95">here</a>.</p><p>A <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2019/03/Paul-Li-MSR-Tech-Report.pdf">Microsoft technical report</a> pinpoints 54 attributes of great software engineers.</p><p>A new report from <i>The Economist </i>lays out <a href="https://www.economist.com/technology-quarterly/2024/03/27/artificial-intelligence-is-taking-over-drug-development">how AI is changing drug development</a>.</p><p>Are you sick of hearing about AI? What topics or technologies would you rather hear us talk about? Email us at <a href="mailto:podcast@stackoverflow.com">podcast@stackoverflow.com</a> or DM Ben <a href="https://twitter.com/benpopper?lang=en">here</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/0ec166a0-3abf-44bc-b93c-ade54327f428/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=0ec166a0-3abf-44bc-b93c-ade54327f428&feed=XA_851k3',1712636400,1175,0,689,0),
('e13bdffb-d1a1-429c-83c7-9b1fcfcd75fd',450923,'How do you evaluate an LLM? Try an LLM.',replace('<p>Connect with Michael on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-geden/">LinkedIn</a>. </p><p>Shoutout to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1083266/user1083266">user1083266</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/36/stellar-question">Stellar Question badge</a> with <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9357668/how-to-store-image-in-sqlite-database">How to store image in SQLite database</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/5fdcebc8-e177-4d07-a7b1-1d1ec35e7d92/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=5fdcebc8-e177-4d07-a7b1-1d1ec35e7d92&feed=XA_851k3',1713241200,1975,0,692,0),
('1d7aed91-4b15-4f56-a376-baecba1c6c5d',450923,'Diverting more backdoor disasters',replace('<p>ICYMI: A <a href="https://cybernews.com/editorial/xz-linux-backdoor-explained/">backdoor</a> in XZ, a popular open-source compression utility, highlights the risks of relying on open-source software maintained by small teams. Read more about the cyberattack <a href="https://boehs.org/node/everything-i-know-about-the-xz-backdoor?fbclid=IwAR12WI8Q5mlVTfR96aOj6B6Xm2ulAi---eLS8LelU3w661OlTh70ldF4a-A_aem_ARc8um12YBHJx9eaZlOkyCEYoxlaWtptRPh9w_2mgUOvHDWfOR8YTxwfJANYA96rEoU3Sq2DH0b3EDt6KUDtLQ95">here</a>.</p><p>Apple’s new LLM, <a href="https://appleinsider.com/articles/24/04/09/apples-new-ai-model-could-help-siri-see-how-ios-apps-work">Ferret</a>, could help Siri understand the user interfaces of mobile displays, potentially expanding the capabilities of Apple’s digital assistant. </p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1569632/cheese1756">cheese1756</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/22/great-question">Great Question badge</a> by asking <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15721373/how-do-i-ensure-that-whitespace-is-preserved-in-markdown">How do I ensure that whitespace is preserved in Markdown?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/0d0fddba-1468-4ef8-b775-19a1bb08faac/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=0d0fddba-1468-4ef8-b775-19a1bb08faac&feed=XA_851k3',1712895600,1116,0,691,0),
('ff6f1e6c-a295-46d8-87ab-d9e377f45a56',450923,'Why the creator of Node.js® created a new JavaScript runtime',replace('<p><a href="https://nodejs.org/en">Node.js</a>® is an open-source JavaScript runtime environment.</p><p><a href="https://deno.com/">Deno</a> is an open-source JavaScript, TypeScript, and WebAssembly runtime. Explore the <a href="https://docs.deno.com/runtime/manual">quick start</a> or check out <a href="https://examples.deno.land/">Deno by example</a>, a collection of annotated examples of how to use Deno.</p><p><a href="https://jsr.io/">JSR</a> is an open-source package registry for JavaScript and TypeScript.</p><p>Keep up to date with Ryan on <a href="https://github.com/ry">GitHub</a> or <a href="https://tinyclouds.org/">his blog</a>.</p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/849055/squadrons">Squadrons</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/22/great-question">Great Question badge</a> by asking for a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6838104/pure-javascript-method-to-wrap-content-in-a-div">Pure javascript method to wrap content in a div</a>.</p><p>Chapters:</p><p>00:00: Introduction and Background</p><p>01:08: Creating Node.js</p><p>05:00: JavaScript on the Server Side</p><p>07:23: Impact of Node.js</p><p>09:18: Edge Function System</p><p>12:13: Protecting Against Malicious Use</p><p>16:02: JSR: Alternative to NPM</p><p>31:01: JSR and its Stage</p><p>34:20: Future of JavaScript</p><p>36:19: Closing and Shoutouts</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/c05979b9-8406-4d1b-bbbc-535659624ce9/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=c05979b9-8406-4d1b-bbbc-535659624ce9&feed=XA_851k3',1710822000,1923,0,682,0),
('9590b55f-c2df-477e-8d24-476f2851a9c8',450923,'Your whole repo fits in the context window',replace('<p>AI shops are now releasing LLMs <a href="https://twitter.com/virattt/status/1767307090022760952">optimized for RAG</a>. </p><p>Turn a repo into a prompt for a <a href="https://twitter.com/skirano/status/1767337182837276949">long-context LLM</a>.</p><p><a href="https://perplexity.ai/">Perplexity AI</a> is an AI-powered search and discovery tool.</p><p>Good news for developers: <a href="https://developer.apple.com/support/dma-and-apps-in-the-eu/">Apple will not</a> remove progressive web app support on iOS in the EU.</p><p><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/642706/basil-bourque">Basil Bourque</a> earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> by explaining <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43379533/how-to-get-full-name-of-month-from-date-in-java-8-while-formatting">How to get full name of month from date in Java 8 while formatting</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/11a14c0c-e7ca-4be1-aed1-bb46fb52df51/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=11a14c0c-e7ca-4be1-aed1-bb46fb52df51&feed=XA_851k3',1710476400,1118,0,681,0),
('bec0602c-4d05-497e-ac21-5c87f7f24431',450923,'A leading ML educator on what you need to know about LLMs',replace('<p>Check out Maxime’s three-part <a href="https://github.com/mlabonne/llm-course">LLM course</a>. </p><p>Part 1 “covers essential knowledge about mathematics, Python, and neural networks.</p><p>Part 2 “focuses on building the best possible LLMs using the latest techniques."</p><p>Part 3 “focuses on creating LLM-based applications and deploying them.” </p><p>Read Maxime’s <a href="https://mlabonne.github.io/blog/">blog</a>.</p><p>Follow Maxime on <a href="https://github.com/mlabonne">GitHub</a> or <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/maxime-labonne/?originalSubdomain=uk">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/6890234/nikhil-wagh">Nikhil Wagh</a> earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> by explaining how to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46422374/efficiently-compare-two-sets-in-python">Efficiently compare two sets in Python</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/9fb4e0ec-8c05-42de-b469-b5bb7a39e50e/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=9fb4e0ec-8c05-42de-b469-b5bb7a39e50e&feed=XA_851k3',1709875200,1880,0,679,0),
('a8fe377c-db38-4907-90db-84861d7bdc0c',450923,'Building GenAI features in practice with Intuit Mailchimp',replace('<p>Intuit shares more about their generative AI operating system (GenOS) in <a href="https://medium.com/intuit-engineering/how-to-accelerate-development-velocity-in-the-genai-era-build-a-genos-e71ac2e17b82">this Medium blog</a>. </p><p>If you want to try out generative AI in MailChimp, <a href="https://mailchimp.com/pricing/marketing/">sign up here</a>. </p><p>Learn more about Intuit technology <a href="https://www.intuit.com/technology/?cid=dis_so_clicks_us_ttt-global_aw_fy24pod1%7Calltechaudience_link%7Cnone_intuit-talent">here</a>.</p><p>Many thanks (and a Lifeboat badge) to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/2387977/dherik">Dherik</a> for dropping an answer on <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/52323460/curl-how-can-i-return-0-if-status-is-200/57433225#57433225">cURL: how can I return 0 if status is 200?</a></p><p>Connect with Shivang on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/shivangshah15/">LinkedIn</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/ad4079e6-f309-4284-a2f9-47f5f9deaa19/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=ad4079e6-f309-4284-a2f9-47f5f9deaa19&feed=XA_851k3',1709836178,1209,0,678,0),
